# Valor company-info denylist — EXAMPLE / TEMPLATE
#
# Valor is public, so committed files must never contain your employer name,
# internal Jira project keys, colleague names, or non-placeholder emails.
# This scanner blocks those — but the list of real terms must NOT be committed
# (or the guard itself becomes the leak). So:
#
#   1. Copy this file to `.hygiene/denylist.local`  (git-ignored — never committed).
#   2. Replace the placeholders below with YOUR real terms.
#   3. For CI, set the SAME content as a repo secret named HYGIENE_DENYLIST
#      (Settings -> Secrets and variables -> Actions). One regex per line.
#
# Format: one case-insensitive regex per line. Blank lines and `#` comments ignored.
# Tip: anchor with \b and include the key shape to avoid false positives
# (e.g. `\bACME-\d+` rather than a bare `ACME`).
#
# Placeholders — replace, do not ship as-is:
# acme-corp                # employer / org name
# \bACME-\d+               # internal Jira project keys
# \bJane Roe\b             # colleague names
# \binternal-codename\b    # internal project / repo codenames
